# Deployment preparation and steps.

1st step: Use and check environment variables.

2nd step: Polish and test code. In the optimization and modules section we covered a lot of this. example: lazy loading.

3rd step: ng build --prod. We saw this in the optimizations module we also need to implement AoT (ahead of time) compilation and that's just one of the many optimizations the Angular CLI does.
It needs to be as small as possible so the user has to download as little as possible.

4th Step: Generate files to a static host. What is a static host? It's a web server capable of running HTML, JS, and CSS but nothing else.